---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Books";
const description = "Long-form work extending beyond the page.";
---

<Layout
  title={title}
  description={description}
>
  <section class="books-page" data-pagefind-body>

    <h1>Exit Wounds</h1>

    <p>
      A collection of poetry exploring recovery, identity, and the mechanics of breaking patterns that reinforce harm. The work traces a toxic relationship with both a person and a substance, alongside a period of homelessness captured in pieces like “Room 223” and “11am.” Written to move from observation to agency.
    </p>

    <blockquote class="poem">
      You called it a bond.
      <br /><br />
      I call it a house made of mirrors,
      <br />
      every room shaped like your absence.
      <br /><br />
      A devotion with a detonator
      <br />
      tucked inside a kiss.
      <br /><br />
      The worst thing you ever did
      <br />
      was make me apologize
      <br />
      for drowning in water
      <br />
      you swore wasn’t there,
      <br />
      from a well you never meant to fill.
    </blockquote>

    <p class="meta">
      Independent publisher · Hardcover
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Available on Amazon
      </a>
    </p>

  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .books-page {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .books-page p,
  .books-page blockquote {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .books-page .poem {
    margin: 2rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    border-left: 2px solid #d6d9df;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .books-page .meta {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: #5f6876;
  }
</style>